%N A112590 Lengths of the loop of the sequences "Sum of last n digits" beginning with (n-1) zeros followed by digit 9.
%e A112590 a(3)=10 because the sum of last three *digits* of the sequence beginning with 0,0,9, (two zeros followed by a 9) enters in a loop whose length is 10 terms; so a(3)=10.
%e A112590 a(4)=1 because "Sum of last four digits" beginning with 0,0,0,9 enters in a cycle of one term (the same term repeated).
